This paper discusses game theory concepts such as Nash equilibria and optimal strategies, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the Traveler's Dilemma, which is a classic problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses mathematical analysis and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between commitment optimal strategies and Nash equilibria, which is a topic that falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
